value.string: Unique opportunity in the heart of Wailuku Town & Seller Financing Now Available! This property consists of two consolidated lots totaling 1/4 acre with three identical 3 bedroom, 1 bath classic Hawaiian bungalows built in 1927, each with a lanai entry plus a one-car garage: 2066, 2074 & 2080 Waikahe Place. The property is in the Wailuku Redevelopment Area (WRA)-Business/Multi-Family Zoning District, allowing a multitude of options for future use. Tucked away just off Vineyard St, it is a block from the Iao Theater and downtown Wailuku. The property is set up high and slopes down at the back, giving beautiful views of Mauna Kahalawai, Happy Valley & the ocean. The homes are vacant and will require lots of TLC to bring them back to habitable condition, so will not likely qualify for conventional financing (other than a renovation loan.) Due to their age, the homes should be considered non-conforming to current zoning & building codes; buyers & their representatives are advised to thoroughly investigate all pertinent facts and complete thorough due-diligence to determine if this property will suit buyer's intended use. Please do not trespass on this property without an appointment; the owners, agents and representatives will not be responsible if you disregard this request.

Incredible value for this ocean view 3BR/3BA custom designed home at Mapulehu, 15 miles from Kaunakakai and 3 miles from the Pukoo Fire Station. House is approximately 250' from the ocean and is elevated on large cement columns. Imperial plaster on the interior walls and large bifold glass doors leading to a large Brazilian hardwood deck. High ceilings and top of the line cabinetry.

This is a Fannie Mae/Home Path asset. Very easy to show in short notice so please schedule a private showing immediately. Asset offers FRESH interior paint, new carpets and some new lighting features. The home sits on the OCEAN side of the street and offers both OCEAN and mountain views from the back yard. With inventory LOW and buyer demand HIGH, this great Wailuku home is a great opportunity.

SPECTACULAR VIEW HOME ON LARGE LOT. MASTER SUITE ON MAIN FLOOR HAS VIEW OF OCENA AND MOUNTAINS. KITCHEN HAS A LARGE ISLAND. ENTERTAIN WITH THE WET BAR DOWN STAIRS IN FAMILY ROOM. LARGE DECKS. CLOSE TO SCHOOLS, PARKS AND SHOPPING. BANK OWNED

Picture yourself sitting on your slate covered lanai overlooking the beautiful Pacific Ocean. Majestic views of Haleakala and the central valley await. Over 3800 sf of well designed space is waiting for your own design consideration. The master bedroom and on-suite are located on the main floor for your convenience. The living room boasts a 28 ft high vaulted ceiling with open walkway above, a beautiful wrought iron baluster lining the hardwood staircase heading upstairs to the remaining bedrooms, bathrooms and the family/entertainment room. All the rooms throughout the home are very distinctive with plush carpeting, brazilian eucalyptus and tile flooring. You will also enjoy the gourmet kitchen with high end appliances, granite counters and the adjoining breakfast nook also overlooking the pacific and rolling pastureland. This development is horse friendly and located just 16 minutes past the town of Waihee. The drive is one you will enjoy even though you will not want to leave this idyllic location perched within the West Maui mountains.
